1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,340
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

2
00:00:02,340 --> 00:00:04,960
 Brothers and sisters, good morning.

3
00:00:04,960 --> 00:00:11,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

4
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:15,440
 To begin today, I would like to tell you a very simple story.

5
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:19,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

6
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:21,920
 There was a high school boy.

7
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:23,480
 His name is Jimmy.

8
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:35,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

9
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:39,200
 He came from a poor family and was very quiet.

10
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:43,040
 Every day, he would walk alone with a large stack of books,

11
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:46,040
 and almost no classmates would talk to him.

12
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:52,240
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

13
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:55,160
 In other people's eyes, he was a little bit strange,

14
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:59,760
 almost like a transparent person with a very low presence.

15
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:06,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

16
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:08,600
 One day after school, he was carrying a whole stack

17
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:12,280
 of books on his way home, as usual.

18
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:16,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

19
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:19,520
 Several classmates walked over and suddenly bumped into him

20
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:20,880
 on purpose.

21
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:25,680
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

22
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,360
 Books and stationery were all scattered

23
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:30,800
 on the ground, everywhere.

24
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:33,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

25
00:01:33,960 --> 00:01:36,600
 People around him just smiled, and then they

26
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:38,720
 separate ways and walk away.

27
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:43,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

28
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:45,880
 At this moment, there was a classmate

29
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:47,640
 standing right beside him.

30
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:49,200
 He could just pretend that he actually

31
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:51,000
 did not see everything happen.

32
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,720
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

33
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:56,400
 But he felt a small sense of gratitude.

34
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:58,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

35
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:01,440
 He thought, should I go over and help?

36
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:03,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

37
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:06,200
 So he went over and scattered them.

38
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:10,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

39
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:14,400
 Helped Jimmy to pick up his books one by one.

40
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:18,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

41
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,880
 And asked him, are you OK?

42
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:21,840
 Where do you live?

43
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,680
 Do you want to come along with me?

44
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:30,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

45
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,720
 It's just a very simple action.

46
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:35,600
 Just walk with him for a while and chat with him for a bit.

47
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:42,160
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

48
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,360
 Gradually, they'd become friends.

49
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:47,840
 And he invited the boy to play basketball with him

50
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:50,000
 and participate in activities together.

51
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:55,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

52
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:59,720
 For this student, that day was just a very small episode

53
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:01,160
 in the day.

54
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:05,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

55
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,880
 But years later, he suddenly realized

56
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:11,360
 that that day had changed Jimmy's life.

57
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:16,160
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

58
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:19,160
 At the graduation ceremony, Jimmy stood on the stage

59
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:20,520
 and gave a speech.

60
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:25,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

61
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:28,440
 He said the reason why he brought all the books home

62
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:31,280
 from school that day was because--

63
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:36,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

64
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:39,880
 It was because he had already prepared to end his life

65
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:41,000
 that weekend.

66
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

67
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:47,080
 Books no longer needed to be left at school anymore.

68
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:51,080
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

69
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:55,800
 However, that afternoon, when the classmates walked over--

70
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:58,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

71
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:02,360
 He knelt down to help him pick up the books one by one

72
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,360
 and walk him home.

73
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:06,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

74
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:08,720
 That was the first time he truly felt--

75
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:12,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

76
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:15,440
 It turns out that there are people in this world who

77
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:17,800
 see me and care about me.

78
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:20,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

79
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:24,560
 It's through this gradual acceptance and care that--

80
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:29,920
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

81
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:32,000
 This weighed him from taking his own life

82
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,880
 and led him down to a completely different path.

83
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:40,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

84
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:44,200
 Brothers and sisters, what may seem like this

85
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,640
 is a very small action to us--

86
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:58,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

87
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:02,040
 A greeting, a smile, a moment of companionship,

88
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:05,560
 this can all be the turning point in one's person's life,

89
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:08,440
 the transition from death to life.

90
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

91
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:14,720
 Today, we're going to take a look at Gospel of John.

92
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:23,000
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

93
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:27,000
 Let's take a look how God uses seemingly very small things

94
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,840
 in our daily life to touch people's heart

95
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:31,640
 and even change their whole life.

96
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:39,160
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

97
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,640
 In John number two, Jesus did something

98
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:46,680
 that seemed insignificant, yet it revealed the glory of God.

99
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:55,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

100
00:05:55,120 --> 00:06:09,240
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

101
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:12,360
 When I was really young, I heard about this interpretation

102
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:15,040
 of a scripture in church.

103
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:18,640
 Jesus is a God who can change matter,

104
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:23,800
 able to transform water, H2O, into alcohol, C2H5O,

105
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:27,160
 adding many more carbon and hydrogen atoms.

106
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:44,480
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

107
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:48,520
 Jesus is truly amazing, a God who can change matter.

108
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:52,320
 However, today, if we consider Jesus' situation

109
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:55,920
 in the Gospel of John and the author's description of Jesus

110
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:58,680
 performing his first miracle--

111
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:06,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

112
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:10,000
 --we will discover that this God is not only

113
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:14,160
 a God who changes matter, but even more so,

114
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:18,080
 a God who changes people's hearts.

115
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:23,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

116
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:25,160
 Let's look at the first miracle Jesus

117
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:28,880
 performed in Gospel of John.

118
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:43,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

119
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:47,160
 On the third day, there was a wedding at Cana in Calili.

120
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:49,200
 The mother of Jesus was there.

121
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:53,800
 Jesus also was invited to the wedding with his disciples.

122
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:57,160
 When the wine ran out, the mother of Jesus said to him,

123
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:59,480
 they have no wine.

124
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:20,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

125
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,600
 And Jesus said to her, woman, what

126
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,880
 does this have to do with me?

127
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:28,480
 My hours has not yet come.

128
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:33,480
 His mother said to the servants, do whatever he tells you.

129
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:36,640
 Now, there were six stone water jars

130
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:40,160
 there for the Jewish rites of purification,

131
00:08:40,160 --> 00:08:42,400
 each holding 20 or 30 gallons.

132
00:08:45,640 --> 00:09:12,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

133
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:16,280
 Jesus said to the servant, fill the jars with water.

134
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,440
 And they filled them up to the brim.

135
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:21,960
 And he said to them, now, draw some out and take it

136
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,920
 to the master of the feast.

137
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:25,760
 So they took it.

138
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:28,760
 When the master of the feast tasted the water,

139
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:32,600
 now it become wine and did not know where it came from,

140
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:36,640
 though the servants who had drawn the water knew it.

141
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:40,000
 And the master of the feast called the bridegroom.

142
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

143
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:17,800
 And said to him, everyone serves the good wine first.

144
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:21,520
 And when people have drunk freely, then the poor wine.

145
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:24,520
 But you have kept the good wine till now.

146
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:30,000
 This, the first of his signs, Jesus did at Cana in Galilee

147
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,360
 and manifested his glory.

148
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,760
 And his disciples believed in him.

149
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:37,720
 After this, he went down to Capernaum

150
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:41,200
 with his mother and his brothers and his disciples.

151
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:44,800
 And they stayed there for several days.

152
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,000
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

153
00:10:46,000 --> 00:11:00,680
 Why did Jesus' mother said to him, they have no more wine?

154
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:03,840
 And why did Jesus react so strong?

155
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:05,000
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

156
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

157
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:26,920
 In Jewish culture at the time, a wedding feast without wine

158
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:30,640
 was a profound humiliation, seen as failure

159
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:35,880
 on the part of the groom's family, a breach of etiquette,

160
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:40,480
 and a social disaster that will be remembered for a lifetime.

161
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

162
00:11:41,880 --> 00:12:07,920
 Mary, Jesus' mom, was likely a relative or very close friend.

163
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:11,880
 Her being mentioned first and seemingly moving in and out

164
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:14,200
 of the inner court suggests that she

165
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:18,280
 was more concerned with the host's reputation and glory

166
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:24,920
 than others, keenly noticing the underlying difficulties.

167
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:26,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

168
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:44,520
 This reflects her initial belief in Jesus' ability to act.

169
00:12:44,520 --> 00:12:48,480
 Secondly, her expectation that Jesus could help

170
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,960
 restore the host family glory.

171
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,240
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

172
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:10,840
 Jesus responded, woman, what does this have to do with me?

173
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:12,880
 My time has not come yet.

174
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:16,400
 Mary's expectation was that Jesus' intervention

175
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:21,120
 indirectly influenced Jesus to reveal God's glory.

176
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

177
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:40,120
 In the Gospel of John, time is a crucial word.

178
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:44,120
 When mentioned, it's usually associated with glory.

179
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:48,240
 Because Jesus knew that when he performed a miracle,

180
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:50,520
 he would reveal God's glory.

181
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:54,200
 Therefore, Jesus' reaction was quite urgent.

182
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

183
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:15,720
 But what Jesus did next transformed

184
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:19,920
 the most uncleaned water, the most despised water,

185
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:24,200
 into something that would bring glory to his master

186
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:27,480
 and to Jesus himself.

187
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

188
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:37,240
 Versus six.

189
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:40,640
 According to the Jewish ritual of purification,

190
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:44,440
 there were six stone jaws placed there.

191
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

192
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:58,520
 Some Chinese English translation

193
00:14:58,520 --> 00:15:03,760
 rendered this as a stone jaw used for Jewish purification

194
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:05,560
 rituals.

195
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:06,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

196
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:25,080
 In fact, Jews placed great importance

197
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:27,880
 on cleanliness rituals because they

198
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:31,720
 understand that cleanliness regulations God

199
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:38,360
 gave in Exodus and Leviticus were intended

200
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:41,720
 to show the world that Jewish people belong

201
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:43,920
 to Jehovah and to God.

202
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

203
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:54,600
 Therefore, all the derived purification rituals

204
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:59,400
 are meant to show one's relationship with God.

205
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

206
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:18,960
 Even today, if you have the opportunity

207
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:22,840
 to visit Western Wall in Jerusalem,

208
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:26,240
 you will see Jews still observing purification

209
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:29,480
 rituals in front of the Western Wall.

210
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:32,920
 There is a hand washing station with a sewer

211
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:35,200
 cup in the basin.

212
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:36,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

213
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:55,920
 They use that sewer cup to hold water,

214
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:58,640
 symbolizing the stone jaws of the pest

215
00:16:58,640 --> 00:17:01,960
 to clean their hands before going to see God,

216
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:05,440
 thus demonstrating their belonging to God.

217
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:08,920
 Therefore, you can imagine how much importance Jews

218
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:12,120
 place on purification rituals.

219
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:13,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

220
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:17,960
 When you came to see God today, did you

221
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:21,120
 get the chance to wash your hands and face?

222
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:22,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

223
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,720
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

224
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:41,320
 Jesus, however, used the stone jaw

225
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:45,840
 used for purification rites to fill them and turn the water

226
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:47,360
 into wine.

227
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:52,800
 This shattered the Jewish and the disciples' preconceived

228
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:56,120
 notion about the purification rites.

229
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:57,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

230
00:17:57,760 --> 00:18:12,480
 The jaws used for purification were actually

231
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:15,000
 filled with uncleanliness.

232
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,520
 Imagine the water in those jaws was

233
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:22,080
 used for washing hands, face, and even feet.

234
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:23,720
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

235
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:29,240
 People came from all directions, traveling long distance

236
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:31,840
 to this wedding feast.

237
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

238
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:40,400
 And at that time, technology wasn't as advanced

239
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,800
 as it is now.

240
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,840
 Many people weren't wearing shoes.

241
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:46,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

242
00:18:50,320 --> 00:18:53,000
 You can imagine how filthy and unclean

243
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,640
 that water could be, filled with mud.

244
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:57,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

245
00:18:57,040 --> 00:19:09,280
 But Jesus transformed these most unclean and filthy water

246
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:12,240
 into the finest wine, better than any wine

247
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:14,920
 served at the entire wedding feast.

248
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:16,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

249
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:25,720
 Here, Jesus not only changed the material itself,

250
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:29,320
 but also shattered the stereotype of cleanliness,

251
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:33,640
 turning the unclean water meant to be received into a tool

252
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:35,720
 to glorify Jesus.

253
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:36,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

254
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:50,720
 Glorify Jesus.

255
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:52,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

256
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:58,600
 So on the level of personal spiritual life--

257
00:19:58,600 --> 00:19:59,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

258
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:16,520
 These water jars were originally intended for ritual purification,

259
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:21,360
 symbolizing how people use our behavior and religious rituals

260
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:25,840
 to slightly cover up their own defilement.

261
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:27,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

262
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:38,280
 Jesus, however, turned the water into wine,

263
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:42,440
 symbolizing that he used his own blood and his own life

264
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:47,520
 to become the true source of purity for humanity.

265
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:48,920
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

266
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:17,200
 The most shameful, unspeakable, and unclean parts of our lives,

267
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:22,440
 whether failure, addictions, sins, or broken relationship,

268
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:27,280
 are not forgotten in the gospel, but transformed by him

269
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:31,240
 into good stories that testify to his grace.

270
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:32,440
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

271
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

272
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:53,800
 In the grace of Christ, we can learn

273
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:57,800
 to surrender our most unbearable moments,

274
00:21:57,800 --> 00:22:01,600
 no longer cover them up with religious rituals

275
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:06,520
 or superficial good deeds, but allowing the blood of Jesus

276
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:10,120
 to truly enter and renew us.

277
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:11,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

278
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:35,080
 There are some things, people and relationship,

279
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:38,000
 that we might not even want to recall,

280
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:42,120
 feeling they are too painful to look back on.

281
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:45,440
 We might think that the time will heal all the wounds,

282
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:48,480
 that they will simply fade away.

283
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:49,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

284
00:22:49,800 --> 00:23:00,960
 Sometimes we might be able to cover up these things

285
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:05,880
 with outward act of kindness or even righteous, religious

286
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:08,920
 righteous.

287
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

288
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:26,440
 But Jesus' most unexpected action

289
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:29,840
 was to transform these most unclean water,

290
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:33,760
 representing our most unspeakable moments in life,

291
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:37,520
 into an instrument for glorifying God.

292
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:38,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

293
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:51,480
 If we are willing to offer it, we

294
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:55,800
 can expect God to transform our unbearable moments in life

295
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:59,400
 into moments and tools for his own glory.

296
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

297
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:03,840
 Do you want to do it?

298
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:05,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

299
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:12,320
 When we talk about work, we expect

300
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:16,880
 God to intervene in our works as well.

301
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:18,240
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

302
00:24:18,240 --> 00:24:27,600
 I don't know, starting from when,

303
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:31,920
 we've begun to lose the hope in God's presence in our lives

304
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:33,360
 and work.

305
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:34,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

306
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:39,920
 Our only hope might be just, let me finish today's work

307
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:41,360
 as quick as possible.

308
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:42,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

309
00:24:53,360 --> 00:24:57,880
 Just like the jewel of gold, even on important occasions

310
00:24:57,880 --> 00:25:02,240
 like weddings, we perform numerous purification rites,

311
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:09,120
 just completing these elaborated rites is exhausted itself.

312
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:10,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

313
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:29,760
 I don't know starting from when, we've

314
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:33,440
 stopped expecting God to intervene in our work.

315
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:37,320
 It is as if our work has nothing to do with God.

316
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:39,360
 I'm just here to earn money.

317
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:42,600
 I'm just here to need a job to support my family.

318
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:46,800
 Besides that, my job has no other meaning.

319
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:48,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

320
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:55,080
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

321
00:25:55,080 --> 00:26:04,720
 What is the most astonishing here about Jesus

322
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:09,920
 is that he transformed the water used for washing feet, which

323
00:26:09,920 --> 00:26:14,600
 is the jewels despised and considered utterly meaningless

324
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:18,960
 into a source of glory for the host and for himself.

325
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:20,080
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

326
00:26:24,360 --> 00:26:29,960
 Seemingly, he would turn the seemingly meaningless work

327
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:34,920
 in our lives into a means to glorify himself.

328
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:37,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

329
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:39,440
 The question is, are you willing to let

330
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:41,800
 God intervene in our lives?

331
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,080
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

332
00:26:54,360 --> 00:26:59,080
 Or we just simply want God to leave us alone.

333
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:02,360
 Let's have more expectations and think more about how

334
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:06,040
 God can intervene in our work.

335
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:07,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

336
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:17,800
 In our faith practice, our sinner life must become real.

337
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:19,080
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

338
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:29,920
 This water was prepared according

339
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:33,600
 to Jewish ritual of purification and is

340
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:36,880
 a part of the Old Testament ritual system.

341
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:38,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

342
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:55,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

343
00:27:55,360 --> 00:28:04,640
 Jesus did not use new vessels, but worked directly

344
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:09,360
 in these purification jars, turning the water into wine.

345
00:28:09,360 --> 00:28:13,240
 This symbolized that he did not add a bunch of new rules,

346
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:17,040
 but rather directed all the purification, sacrifice,

347
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:19,520
 and festivals of the Old Testament

348
00:28:19,520 --> 00:28:23,840
 to a salvation he accomplished on the cross.

349
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:25,160
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

350
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:40,760
 For the church, this sign calls on people

351
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:44,320
 not to merely outwardly observe righteous,

352
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:48,920
 but to enter into the abundant faith in Christ.

353
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:50,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

354
00:28:50,120 --> 00:29:06,760
 Worship, baptism, communion, and fellowship,

355
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:10,560
 if they lose the inner reality of being cleansed and renewed

356
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:15,800
 in Christ, these may be just reduced to mere righteous.

357
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:34,440
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

358
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:37,080
 In this miracle, Jesus invites us

359
00:29:37,080 --> 00:29:41,560
 to prepare empty jars in every festival and gathering,

360
00:29:41,560 --> 00:29:46,360
 trusting in his intervention and waiting for him

361
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:49,200
 to transform ordinary water and ordinary life

362
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:52,760
 into wine full of grace and joy.

363
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:55,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

364
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:59,240
 Remember the story that I mentioned at the beginning?

365
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:00,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

366
00:30:00,600 --> 00:30:10,680
 Jimmy stopped his suicidal thoughts

367
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:14,160
 because someone showed him a small act of kindness

368
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:16,000
 by wanting to take care of him.

369
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

370
00:30:17,280 --> 00:30:24,640
 This is actually a result of God making

371
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:27,120
 a person's inner life authentic.

372
00:30:27,120 --> 00:30:28,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

373
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:37,160
 Caring for others isn't about external rules

374
00:30:37,160 --> 00:30:40,080
 and regulations, but a genuine feeling

375
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:42,640
 from the depth of one's heart.

376
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:44,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

377
00:30:44,320 --> 00:30:50,360
 God used this small act to save a person's life.

378
00:30:50,360 --> 00:30:51,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

379
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:59,480
 Transforming an ordinary life into a wine full of surprises.

380
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:00,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

381
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:01,200
 Let's pray together.

382
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:12,080
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

383
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:15,760
 Dear Heavenly Father, thank you not only

384
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:18,880
 for changing the material world, but also

385
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:21,720
 for changing our inner lives.

386
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:23,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

387
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:35,440
 Let us learn and look forward to you transforming

388
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:38,600
 the hardships and brokenness in our lives

389
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:41,080
 into witness to your glory.

390
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:43,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

391
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:48,000
 We pray in the name of Lord Jesus, amen.

392
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:50,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

